{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0afe462d-0edc-482c-910d-ee411ed6bbff","content":"Here's a quick overview of common web API templates and auth options:\n\n**ASP.NET Core** (`dotnet new webapi`)\n- `--auth` options: `None`, `Individual` (Identity/JWT), `IndividualB2C` (Azure AD B2C), `SingleOrg` (Azure AD), `Windows`\n\n**Node.js/Express** — no built-in CLI template, but common auth approaches:\n- Passport.js (JWT, OAuth2, local)\n- express-jwt / jsonwebtoken\n\n**Python/FastAPI or Flask** — common auth:\n- OAuth2 with JWT (FastAPI has built-in security utilities)\n- Flask-Login, Flask-JWT-Extended\n\n**Java/Spring Boot** (`spring init`):\n- Spring Security with JWT, OAuth2, LDAP, SAML\n\nFor example, to scaffold a .NET API with JWT-based auth:\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual -o MyApi\n```\n\nWould you like me to scaffold a specific project for you?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4050ff47-8a98-4f40-84ac-bc7810cb688b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - I can answer from my knowledge of common web frameworks.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the most popular frameworks.","outputTokens":302},"id":"bdc5363b-7e81-4fe3-847b-61202108abc2","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:48:21.270Z","parentId":"25d413cc-59eb-41ed-9f78-d0e8df4441cc"}
